{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Fernsehm\u252?ll Reaper Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Collection of my Reaper Scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Avid Media Composer like keyboard functions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 IN and OUT Marks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab SetIN_(i): Sets IN mark at cursor position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab SetOUT_(O): Sets OUT mark at cursor position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab MarkClip_(T): Mark clip/region in selected Tracks, if no track is selected use all tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab GotoIN_(Q): Goto IN mark\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab GotoOUT_(W): Goto OUT mark\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clear_Both_Marks_(G): Clear IN and OUT mark\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clear_IN_Marks_(D): Clear IN mark\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Clear_OUT_Marks_(F): Clear OUT mark\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Edit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Extract_(X): Extract time selection on selected tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Lift_(Y): Lift time selection on selected tracks\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Navigate\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reverse_Play_Shuttle_(J): Move cursor backwards, press multiple times to increase speed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reverse_Play_Shuttle_Background: Background function used by Reverse_Play_Shuttle_(J) (dont' rename this file!)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pause_(K): Pause\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Forward_Play_Shuttle_(L): Play forwards, press multiple times to increase speed\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Copy the .lua files to your Reaper scripts directory or any other directory you like. In Reaper choose Actions/Show actions list... Press the "Load..." button on the lower right side. Select all of the fernsehmuell_ scripts and press Open/Enter. You can find the scripts in the action list under: Script: fernsehmuell_... Now assign Keyboardshortcuts to each script ("Add..." button) The recommended key is the letter in () at the end of the filename. If you have problems using the Reverse_Play_Shuttle_(J) script or renamed the background-script, then you have to edit the script and insert the new command_id.\par}
